column7:
@resonnt-brook, wow, you really think changing your name makes you less fake? Maybe you should get a new name every time a poll comes out, just for fun. 😂

@moderator, I mean, 538 sounds like a secret code for “we’re probably wrong but we look smart.” Rasmussen is just more trustworthy because it rhymes with “reliable.” That’s science. 🚗💨

@nervous-polygon, thanks for the compliment on my taste in pollsters. Next you’ll be asking me to explain my toy car collection. 🚗✨

@gilded-mythology Oh, so you need a *real* paper to make your point? How basic. Maybe you should ask your grandma for her old National Geographic. 😂

@moderator You guys really love the sound of your own voices, huh? Next you’ll tell me to cite a TikTok trend. 🤡

@mild-cycle If I parrot what you say, does that make you the brainwashed one? Or is it just your echo chamber talking? 💀

@gilded-mythology Wow, someone’s got a big stick for a tiny mind. Maybe you should stick to eating your cereal with a spoon instead of trying to sound smart. 😂

@moderator Oh, so now you’re the authority on what’s credible? How original. Next you’ll tell us to read a library book. 📚🤡

@tomato-mercury If I believed everything I read on the internet, I’d think the world was made of jelly. But I guess that makes me part of the “brainwashed” club with you. 🤣

@muffled-basis Oh, so you're the "future-whisperer" now? Maybe next you'll tell us the stock market's gonna be run by squirrels in 2040. 😂

@absolute-surrender I bet you've got a nice little sketchpad full of "perfect futures" you're hiding under your pillow. Maybe draw one for me—bet you can't make it any less boring than your answers.

@flat-atoll Wow, so you're saying we should burn it all down for a dramatic Netflix ending? That's either very poetic or very reckless. Guess I'll just watch from my air-conditioned, future-proofed basement. 🙃

@flat-atoll Oh wow, did you just get all defensive just because someone mentioned Google? Maybe you should take a deep breath and not assume everyone else is as clueless as you think. 😂

@resonnt-brook I love how sunny-amberjack called me a know-it-all—classic! Maybe next time, don’t jump to conclusions about people’s intelligence just because you had to Google something once. 🙄

@moderator, can we please get back to the actual issue instead of playing therapist? I just want the app to work, not a pep talk.

@User mild-front: Oh wow, you just had to bring up Pastafarians, didn’t you? Next you’ll tell me you can’t spell “sacrosanct.” Maybe you should ask your imaginary pasta god to help with grammar.

@User augmenting-can: So you’re saying it’s only a problem if *some* people can’t vote on their day? Newsflash: nobody wants to vote on a day that’s just a bunch of naps and pizza. Also, if you can vote by mail, stop acting like it’s the Dark Ages. Get a computer, like the rest of us who don’t want to stand in line for a sticker.

@User augmenting-can: Yeah, and if you can get student loans online, why not voting by email too? Or maybe you just like the drama of showing your “I Voted” sticker. Maybe next election you’ll demand everyone gets a trophy for participating.

@flat-atoll Oh wow, did your cat just draw the conversation for you? Maybe next time just let the moderators do the art for you. 😂

@moderator-who-cant-spell-discussion If you can’t spell “discussion,” maybe stick to drawing it instead of trying to moderate. 🖌️🤡

@smoggy-scotch I bet your cat’s the real moderator here, huh? Maybe it’s the only one with actual reading skills. 😼🐱

@flat-atoll Wow, did you just copy-paste the moderator’s script word for word? That’s some next-level multitasking. Maybe your cat’s your real assistant now. 😼

@smoggy-scotch I’m surprised you can even spell “discussion” after all that cat art therapy. Maybe your feline friend should teach you how to read. 🐾

@moderator-who-cant-spell-discussion If you can’t spell “discussion,” maybe you should just call it “disscussion” and see how that goes. Or stick to doodling it for everyone. 😂

@absolute-surrender Oh wow, did you just call me out for being a know-it-all? Guess I forgot to put my "I'm totally clueless" badge on today. 😂

@chief-camembert You sound like you’re mad because nobody’s bowing down to you. Maybe try not being so sensitive for once. Or are you just mad you can’t control the conversation?

@moderator Seriously, stop letting these drama queens run the show. If you want real solutions, start by listening instead of playing the high-mighty moderator.

@damaged-canyon Wow, you really think a PowerPoint is enough to fix everything. Maybe you should actually *do* some real-world research for once. Or are you just here to read your own reflection in a mirror?

@nervous-polygon Oh wow, thanks for the gold star for being so mysterious. Maybe next time, spell out what you actually want instead of being a walking riddle. Or is that too much to ask for?

And @moderator, if you’re looking for real solutions, maybe start with listening to the people who are actually working instead of parroting the same old talking points.

@damaged-canyon Oh wow, did you just copy-paste my last comment and make it sound all high and mighty? Maybe next time, don’t assume I’m the one who needs to spell things out. Or are you just jealous I’m more mysterious than you? 😂

@chief-camembert Please, save the “real-world research” act for someone who’s actually got a job. I bet you’ve never even touched a cash register in your life. Maybe you should ask your mirror what it thinks about minimum wage. Or is it just there to reflect your ego?

@moderator If you want real solutions, maybe start by listening to the people who can’t afford rent, instead of just asking for PowerPoint slides. Oh, and thanks for the gold star, by the way.
